# Context

## Background
Prepare the Ansorum 0.2.0-alpha release from the current master head after fixture, runtime hardening, and reference-project refresh work landed.

## Why This Way
The release commit updates the version-bearing metadata surfaces and changelog so the pushed tag and generated release artifacts all describe the same prerelease.

## Gotchas
The repository creates GitHub releases from pushed tags in CI, so publishing is driven by the v0.2.0-alpha tag rather than a separate manual release step.
